body: in your display/power settings, do you have any sort of timer for low power mode/sleep or such?

Thanks for getting back to me! 

I looked through all the power management settings and I couldn't find anything that would cause this, to the best of my knowledge. To be clear, the terminal doesn't close and the computer doesn't shut down, ipython just stops.
I have never seen this behavior -- perhaps try updating your ipython etc.
The same thing happened to me and stops at 872 iterations.

I'm afraid that this is not a DeepLabCut issue. It might be CUDA/TF/your hardware/ etc. 

Can you train on your CPU for more iterations?

Seems a windows only issue; now reported here (#463), and #468 https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut/issues/479#issuecomment-549919559

Can all of you report:

CUDA version, TensorFlow Version, and how you are running the code (ipython, python, GUI, jupyter notebook, etc).
Same problem. win10, cudatoolkit-10.0.130, tensorflow-1.13.1, jupyter lab, CUDA-10.1, nvidia driver-441.12

Strange. Can you please share your complete conda environment so we can try to reproduce this.

Sorry forgot to send the env file. 
[environment.zip](https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut/files/3814985/environment.zip)

@wyattray1364 CUDA >10 will not work. Currently only up to CUDA 10 with TF 1.14 is supported. https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut/blob/master/docs/installation.md#the-most-common-new-user-hurdle-is-installing-and-using-your-gpu

please also see #468 

This turns out to be a size issue of the GPU, as mobileNet worked, and gpu was full. Please note we recommend a 1080 ti or higher, as most lab-applications use larger frames sizes, and the gpu memory size becomes very important for performance.
This might be due to a corrupt image (see other issue), or an erroneous installation of TF.
